{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"020e68ef-98f7-4fd7-991c-d7d3a2e00356","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing file to modify, here's exactly how to convert your page and catch errors at build time.\n\n---\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML**\n\nOn the root `ContentPage`, declare the XML namespace for your viewmodel and set `x:DataType`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe only structural change is:\n- Add `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"`\n- Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`\n\nAll existing `{Binding …}` expressions now resolve **at compile time** against `SettingsViewModel`.\n\n---\n\n**2. Catch binding errors at build time**\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler validates every `{Binding}` path. If you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding FontSze}`), you get a **build error** like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"FontSze\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\nTo ensure this is active:\n\n| Setting | Where | Value |\n|---|---|---|\n| `<EnableXamlC>true</EnableXamlC>` | `.csproj` `<PropertyGroup>` | `true` (default in MAUI) |\n| Treat warnings as errors (optional) | `.csproj` | `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>` |\n\nXAML compilation is **on by default** in .NET MAUI, so adding `x:DataType` is all you need — mismatched property names will fail the build.\n\n**Tip:** If a specific binding must be late-bound (e.g., binding to a dynamic source), opt out locally with `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element to suppress the compile-time check for just that binding.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6ca38c50-26d2-4e94-85c3-ac3f69ddba40","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking about a page they have but it's not in the current directory. Let me check what's in the current directory.","outputTokens":784,"requestId":"D44D:27A376:1C8C542:201BA4E:6A07C100"},"id":"e24726a4-0619-4dfb-9365-2274edc6be89","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:57:51.727Z","parentId":"9eb823bc-7d6a-4ec1-b593-f3e67eaae88d"}
